Some students sustained minor injuries, while around 30 remain hospitalized. Investigations are ongoing to determine the motive of the suspect, who underwent surgery, and some toy weapons were also found at the explosion site as part of the investigation. The incident has caused a major shock for students and parents.

Al Jazeera’s Jessica Washington reports.

description:
Typhoon Kalmagi sweeps through central Philippines, causing massive flooding, with the town of Iloan in Cebu province recording one of the highest death tolls. Rescue teams continue searching for the missing amid roads blocked by debris and mud, while residents try to clean damaged homes and recover from the losses. More than 3,000 houses have been partially or completely damaged, and floods have destroyed cars and spread through the streets. The government warns of another approaching typhoon from the north threatening the country, forcing residents to prepare for further natural hazards.

Al Jazeera’s Barnaby Lo reports.

description:
A gripping look at journalism’s ultimate sacrifice, told through stories of courage, loss and unwavering conviction.

In a world where truth-telling can often mean life or death, this documentary shines a light on journalists who paid the ultimate price for their work. From war zones to political cover-ups, their courageous reporting exposed critical truths, but also made them targets. Through intimate interviews with their families, friends, and colleagues, the film provides a heartfelt tribute to their legacies while uncovering the dangerous realities of journalism today.

Drawing on rare footage, personal accounts, and expert analysis, the film goes beyond the headlines to explore the human stories behind the statistics. These are not just tales of loss but of bravery, conviction, and an unwavering belief in the public’s right to know. author: Al Jazeera English
description:
Millions of Palestinians in Gaza are facing a severe starvation crisis despite the ceasefire. Daily struggles for water, food, and medicine continue as essential supplies remain scarce. Pharmacies are nearly empty, fresh produce and protein sources are hard to find, and families are forced to make one meal last the entire day.

Aid trucks are not entering Gaza as agreed in the ceasefire, and the limited commercial supplies available are sold at skyrocketing prices. The gap between humanitarian need and reality on the ground continues to widen.

Al Jazeera’s Hani Mahmoud reports.

author: Al Jazeera English
description:
Amjad Shawa, director of the Palestinian NGO Network, discusses the dire humanitarian situation in Gaza following the fragile ceasefire. Despite the halt in daily killings, Gaza faces severe challenges: destroyed homes and infrastructure, limited access to medical and humanitarian aid, blocked crossings, and thousands of displaced families. Essential supplies like tents, winter clothing, blankets, and medical aid remain insufficient. Shawa highlights the critical conditions for children, pregnant women, the elderly, and malnourished families, calling for urgent international support to lift the blockade and deliver much-needed assistance.
